Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a network coding scheme for real-time video transmission, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video transmission and quality adaptation, which is a key aspect of multimedia systems. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the relationship between redundancy ratio and encoding bit rate, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper mentions PSNR (Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio), which is a common metric used in computer vision and image processing. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions Forward Error Correction (FEC), which is a technique used in cryptography and security to ensure data integrity.
